At Kentucky State University, we are committed to student success, faculty and staff professional growth and development, and enriching the lives of the members of the community and the Commonwealth.  As the opening lines of our Mission Statement reflect, “Kentucky State University is a public, comprehensive, historically black land-grant university committed to the Commonwealth of Kentucky.”

We are proud of our heritage in Kentucky and we embrace our traditions of excellence in teaching, scholarship, and service since our founding in 1886.  Over the years, the University “on the hill” has maintained its role as a thriving educational community with a special focus on the liberal arts.  It is within this tradition of excellence and service that we embark on our next strategic plan which will be implemented across 2020 to 2025.

As we move forward with our strategic plan, we will be guided by our shared commitment to innovation, diversity, inclusion, and sustainability.  Our new strategic plan will be the collaborative work of our campus and our community.  We believe that the strategic plan will be revolutionary and evolutionary.  With the new strategic plan, we will gain a fresh blueprint to express who we are as Kentucky State University now and for the future.
The Mission of Kentucky State University

Welcome to Kentucky State University. Located in Frankfort, the state’s capital city, KSU has a 130-year tradition of educating students to make a difference in the world.
Our primary focus is attracting and educating talented students by having a dedicated staff and faculty with the diverse backgrounds and experiences to deliver on that commitment.

Kentucky State University provides a comprehensive education that will not only provide a degree, but will prepare you for a lifetime of learning. Small classes and accessible faculty make Kentucky State a great place to learn and grow.  KSU offers its students a wide variety of great degree options.
Kentucky State to host Green and Gold Day at the Capitol
Kentucky State University is hosting a Green and Gold Day at the Capitol Tuesday, Feb. 4 from noon to 2 p.m. on the mezzanine level of the Capitol building.
Kentucky State University to host annual legislative fish fry
The Kentucky State University College of Agriculture, Communities, and the Environment is hosting its annual legislative fish fry Tuesday, Feb. 25 at 5 p.m. in the Cooperative Extension Building.
Kentucky State University confers nearly 60 degrees at Fall 2019 Commencement Convocation
Nearly 60 Kentucky State University graduates crossed the stage Friday, Dec. 13 during the Fall 2019 Commencement Convocation in Carl H. Smith Auditorium in David H. Bradford Hall.
